Function Reference/wp defer comment counting « WordPress Codex
-----------

Whether to defer comment counting.

When setting \$defer to true, all post comment counts will not be
updated until \$defer is set to false. When \$defer is set to false,
then all previously deferred updated post comment counts will then be
automatically updated without having to call
wp\_update\_comment\_count() after.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_defer_comment_counting( $defer ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$defer` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*)
    Default:

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(unknown)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

Source File
-----------

`wp_defer_comment_counting()` is located in `wp-includes/comment.php`

